# Testing Conventions

## Backend — pytest

### conftest.py DB Fixture

Each test runs in a transaction that is rolled back after the test — no teardown needed.

```python
# backend/tests/conftest.py
@pytest_asyncio.fixture
async def db():
    async with engine.begin() as conn:
        await conn.run_sync(Base.metadata.create_all)
        async with AsyncSession(bind=conn) as session:
            yield session
            await session.rollback()

@pytest_asyncio.fixture
async def client(db):
    app.dependency_overrides[get_db] = lambda: db
    async with AsyncClient(app=app, base_url="http://test") as ac:
        yield ac
```

### respx — Mock Outbound HTTP

Use `respx` to intercept calls made by `recipe-scrapers` / `httpx` so tests never hit real URLs.

```python
@respx.mock
async def test_extract(client, respx_mock):
    respx_mock.get("https://example.com/recipe").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=MOCK_HTML))
    response = await client.post("/api/recipes/extract", json={"url": "https://example.com/recipe"})
    assert response.status_code == 200
```

### Auth in Tests

Override `get_current_user` dependency to inject a fixed test user:

```python
app.dependency_overrides[get_current_user] = lambda: test_user
```

### Coverage Targets

- All API route handlers
- Extractor service (`services/extractor.py`)
- Auth middleware / JWT helpers
- Duplicate detection logic (409 path and override path)

## Frontend — Vitest + Testing Library

### Setup

```tsx
// src/mocks/server.ts
import { setupServer } from 'msw/node';
import { handlers } from './handlers';
export const server = setupServer(...handlers);

// vitest.setup.ts
beforeAll(() => server.listen());
afterEach(() => server.resetHandlers());
afterAll(() => server.close());
```

### Page Test Structure

Every page test covers four states:

```tsx
describe('RecipeDetail', () => {
  it('renders loading state', () => { ... });
  it('renders recipe data on success', async () => { ... });
  it('renders error message on API failure', async () => { ... });
  it('handles user interaction (e.g. edit save)', async () => { ... });
});
```

### 409 Duplicate Detection Test

```tsx
it('shows override modal on 409', async () => {
  server.use(http.post('/api/recipes/extract', () => HttpResponse.json({ detail: '...' }, { status: 409 })));
  // render, submit URL, assert modal appears, click override, assert new request fired
});
```

